      <h3>What I'm Working On</h3>
      <p>If you want a little insight into how I think and work...</p>
      <p>
        <a
          href="https://www.statfoundry.com">StatFoundry</a
        > is an NFL analytics platform I built on a Neo4j graph database. This is
        my "proving ground" for validating the usefulness of new technologies before I suggest them to my clients. Things like RAG, GraphRAG, MCP Servers,
        AI Agents, etc. It's also what led me to develop <a href="/blog/tags/bigrfs">BIGRFS</a> a novel architecture for enabling user friendly query expansion on top of LPGs, and <a href="https:www.github.com/manbradcalf/graphlint">GraphLint</a>, a tool that allows me to run SHACL against any GQL or Cypher compliant LPGs
      </p>

